Tonight’s Monday Night Football Game:

  • Buffalo Bills vs New York Jets
  • Date: Monday, Sept. 11, 2023
  • Time: 8:20 PM ET

StatSalt.com writer Paul Biagioli writes:

Vegas is giving Aaron Rodgers a lot of credit, considering last year’s matchups between these teams finished 20-17 and 20-12. Rodgers would need to add 10 points to the highest point total between these teams last year to cover this line. This is still week 1, and both teams may still be trying out new formations and looks, which can stall drives if the offenses are not clicking. Both teams have strong defenses and will not give up a lot of points early in the season. The Bills only allowed 10 points in Week 1 last year and brought back the majority of their defense. Divisional teams typically play each other close, and we will have a low-scoring battle in this one.

Prediction: Under 46
